=== FINDING REGISTER ===

10.8.3C-F01
  Item: 6.7 -- Share-link surface
  DoD assertion violated: D2 -- test does not prove the 6.7 DoD assertion
  Description: 6_7_share_link_isolation.test.sql asserts NOT_FOUND on expired
  token lookup. The 6.7 migration implemented TOKEN_EXPIRED as the response code
  for expired tokens. The test reflects the current (8.9) state where TOKEN_EXPIRED
  was replaced by NOT_FOUND to prevent existence leaks. This is a version-skew
  finding -- the test is correct for the current system state but does not prove
  the 6.7 DoD assertion as originally specified.
  Recommended remediation: Open a tracking PR to either formally document that
  the 8.9 migration superseded the 6.7 TOKEN_EXPIRED behavior and the test
  correctly reflects the final state, or waive the version-skew finding with
  explicit justification that NOT_FOUND is a security improvement over TOKEN_EXPIRED.
  Tracking PR: REQUIRED before Section 10 close verification (SOP S17)

